                     <sic>wh*</sic>
                     <corr>what's</corr>
                  </choice>
                  <lb/>
that to me? I am not wicked, though <lb/>
I am a sinner, as all men be. Others <lb/>
will think, Its true <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>tha*</sic>
                     <corr>that</corr>
                  </choice> we <choice ana="illegible">
                     <sic>mu*</sic>
                     <corr>must</corr>
                  </choice>
                  <lb/>
Turn from our evil <normalised orig="waies" auto="true">ways</normalised>: but I <lb/>
am Turned long ago; I hope this is <lb/>
                  <pb n="26"/>
                  <lb/>
not now to do. And thus while <lb/>
wicked men think they are not <lb/>
